caption: Everything I have eaten here is really good, good prices. Can't say enough good things about this place, friendly welcoming service
Really good service and food is great. Mexican chicken sandwich is amazing.
I am so glad that we have this place in the neighborhood. Amazing food for great prices. I stop by multiple times a week.
I work a few blocks away and stop in at Brett’s often. Their breakfast breads are a really great price for a tasty breakfast, and their cold cut sandwiches never disappoint.

This place is amazing! Reminds me of the classic diners that I grew up on in New Jersey, except this is a cute little corner version of one. Large menu, fast and friendly service, and great food. Their iced & brewed coffee have great flavor. We ordered a croissant and a bacon egg and cheese sandwich, both are perfect and hearty. We will be back way more often!
Love places like this little corner restaurant pretty large menu. Great food and friendly service. We need to keep places like this in business, especially during these unfortunate times
Food was super flavorful. The staff was very friendly and kind. Prices that are reasonable. Feels similar to a cafe in Chicago I liked.
Delicious selection of cakes and sandwiches! Prices are very reasonable and service was excellent.
Delicious rueben sandwiches!
Love their sandwiches!
Terrific counter service Cafe.  Been coming here for over 25 years.  Still family owned, with food made from scratch.  Love it.
Love the baked goods.  Especially the desert breads.
Good breakfast, I've eaten there many mornings.
Great BLT and nice veggie options
Excellent neighborhood breakfast and lunch spot!
I ordered Tuna Melt sandwich; love it

I have been to this place twice. The first time I ordered a bagel with veggies and they left off the sprouts. Didn’t say they were out didn’t offer a sub. Came back preserved the same thing. I was under the impression it came with CC because that’s how I got the first one. To my dismay it was wrong. I brought it back and kindly asked was it supposed to come with cc. The lady said yes. Then she took my food after just handling cash without washing her hands. Said oh no it doesn’t come with cc. I asked her to please make it again and I will pay for another. She began yelling at me telling me it doesn’t come that way wrapped the food she and the cook to touched and tried to give it back to me. When I told her that was unsanitary and asked for a new sandwich I would pay for l. She snatched the bag off the counter threw it in the garage and screamed at me in front of customers. No apologies no nothing. Just kept yelling I tried I tried. Not only was this embarrassing it was the worst customer service I’ve ever had. Being a restaurant manager for over 10 years this is ridiculous. She is not the person who should be up front with customer if she has anger issues or cannot handle when a customer is dissatisfied. She then told a lady who asked about tofu they had it and they didn’t. This place needs structure!
You need to update your website, you are not open at 6am, and in fact not even 7am!
Good coffee!
Everything is fresh and tasty. They have the best coffee!!
I love their coffee!
Great sandwich spot with a big menu and homemade soups and fresh ingredients.  Very very good.
Still as good as the last time I was there 20 years ago
nice lowkey spot and has delicious food
They have some damn good burgers and corned beef sandwich. In the morning you get yourself a thick slice of banana bread, maddone!!!
Finally decided to start charging for syrup in ICED coffee. You don’t put crystallized sugar in iced coffee. Overall vibe has changed with the new FOH cashier.
Really good hamburger, great price as well. Can get busy but that's because it's worth the wait.
Amazing service AND I could order through the side window when walking my dog. Huge win.

This place is good, quick, and easy. All the employees are really nice. I have never gone for lunch, just for pre work breakfast. I would recommend it. Can seem a bit pricey, but it is the river north area, so what do you expect. They get to know the regulars and start making your order when you come in which is cool. Seems to be a place that cares.
Excellent food you can't go wrong with anything you order. Everything always tastes fresh.
Reasonable prices. Food was good. Just wish there was a few more options for breakfast
Old school breakfast and lunch place. Solid egg plates. Good coffee and pastries
Warm spot on a cold morning, good cup of joe,  tasty eats.
Tasty and affordable.
Fast, and friendly and the chicken salad on white is the platonic ideal of chicken salad sandwiches.
Great little corner diner for a quick coffee, fresh OJ, breakfast, or lunch. Soups, sandwiches, and omelettes are all good options.
Affordable prices, great food, friendly staff!
Food place for a sandwich during lunch break. Nothing special though.
Friendly service, reasonable prices, and a quaint little business located close to the Chicago-Brown line.

Great neighborhood lunch spot. They always have one or two specials a day that are consistently good. This place is a step up in quality compared to other counter-order locations in the city. The staff is as friendly as you need them to be.  Highly recommend: Turkey club Bacon Cheeseburger Corned beef sandwich  Pro tip: Order ahead for pick up to avoid heavy lines during lunch.
Good mexican burrito
I love the sandwiches here. Always fresh and tasty. Definitely get a cookie or a homemade baked good while your there.
Good food great services

I stopped to grab a cup of coffee and some banana bread. The bread was good, fresh, moist, and a huge piece. The coffee was okay, i like mine a bit stronger, I did not ask what the difference was in the Americano coffee and the regular coffee. I have to ask on my next visit. Looks like a place where you can get a home cooked type breakfast, instead of the  premade crap from some other places. I am giving it 3 stars now, but I will be going back to try other menu items.

The coffee is excellent and saves me a trip to Starbucks another block or two north, as I head south 3 blocks into the no coffee or food for non-tourist area.  It's basically the only thing besides Subway and Mixed Greens, a foofoo salad shop between there and the Merchandize Mart.  The donuts are good, and the breakfast always smells fantastic.  But I ordered a breakfast sammich, and is was basically an omelette on toast.  If they used sausage patties instead of chopped links and asked how to finish the egg, would be so worth the pricy charge.  I would just assume to go to the Subway or Rock N Roll McDonald's and get sammich and coffee under $5.  It is convenient, and the only mom & pop show in several blocks.

Excellent family owned sandwich shop with tasty reasonably priced food. They're not getting the fifth star only because it is so small and is always packed during lunch time. It can be difficult to find seats sometimes due to so many people.  Being a meat lover, I've strangely fell in love with the savory goodness that is their Black Bean Burger and order it about once a month, with added bacon. Having came her for several years, I've yet to find anything less than delicious in their menu, but really need to try out their breakfast sandwiches. All in all I'm a huge fan of this place, but the internal space needs to be rethought to make room for more customers. Too much space is wasted.
Overpriced for the quality of the food. Pretty good coffee & pastries.

I come here almost every morning. I get either an iced or hott coffee and a bacon egg cheese sandwich. Great food and great service. It's nice having a place like this in the morning on my walk from the Chicago stop of the brown line. There's no other breakfast places close or better.
Always friendly service. The grilled cheese is fantastic.
Food was excellent!
I like their breakfast sandwiches and lattes. So close to the Chicago brown line stop and the line is not nearly as long as Starbucks! I always feel better supporting a local shop too.
Got pretty sick from an egg salad sandwich I ate from this place. They try to make it a hip place but its pretty run down and the expensive sandwitches arent that good or fresh.
It's real.
Solid burger
The food is excellent and the workers are friendly.
Great food
Nice decent food.
A good breakfast/lunch option. Nice specials

A popular spot which is just so so in my opinion.  I've had a couple sandwiches from here - tuna melt and a vegetarian.  The vegetarian was soggy and not great. And it annoys me that the vegetarian part of their menu includes chicken dishes....  If it were in another part of town, I don think they'd be able to charge $9 for a basic sandwich and be successful.

I fill my reusable bottle here with their fresh brewed Green Tea a lot of mornings on my way to work. They know me by know and don't even have to ask what I want, it is great! I also get a discount more then the 10cents the national chain offers for bringing in my own cup! These guys are always super friendly, I can't say enough good things. I have eaten both breakfast and lunch here as well, great meals all around. Sometimes it can take a bit longer then I'd like to wait for food but it is worth it in the end.

The prices are a little high, but the food is good and made to order. I had the grilled cheese on French bread with a side salad and it was about $11. I've also tried their turkey burgers. It's not a great option at lunch time because it's so small and there's only about 10 tables in there. It's gets packed really quick. They also serve breakfast items, teas, coffee, etc.

Busy, sandwiches and basic lunch fare type joint with a killer convenient location near the brown line.  kind of pricey for the food but worth it for the great location and remarkably fast ordering and eating.

Always great service at Brett's Kitchen.  Their sloppy joes is excellent as well as their sweet potatoes fries.  For faster delivery though during lunch, order ahead because it can be busy at lunchtime.
Good sandwiches but service is a little slow. Very busy at lunch and seating is limited. Decent if you are in the area.
The most hidden gem in River North.  Get the Huevos Rancheros special with an extra egg.  You can thank me later!
One of the best places in River North to grab a reasonably priced lunch. The burgers are the best. The daily specials are always worth trying.

Brett's Kitchen is one of my go to places for a quick lunch or breakfast. The extensive menu includes omelets, sandwiches, salads and other lunch specials. Everything is fresh and made while you wait and you can see them making your food. I love the tuna and the daily specials are usually a good choice too. It can get very busy at lunch time so I usually like to get there before or after the rush.
Great service and excellent baked goods. Try the cafe mocha or the oatmeal with brown sugar.

Customer service at Brett's is terrible.  I placed an order over the phone to go 20 mnutes ahead of time.  When I arrived, the cashier hadn't even placed the order.  She was not friendly and didn't offer an apology.  She said, "You still want it?" I asked if she would discount for the inconvenience.  She said, "No, take it or leave it."  I have eaten there many times before.  The food was fair, but the biggest draw was that it was convenient.  I will have to find something new.
